{"id": 15639, "source": "pestle", "subject": "biology", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2022", "session": "22M", "subtopic": "2-9-photosynthesis", "title": "22M.1.SL.TZ1.12", "topic_id": "2", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>The graph shows how the rate of photosynthesis of a green plant varies with CO<sub>2</sub> concentration at two different light intensities. The temperature is kept constant at 20 °C.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"/></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"> </p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">What is the limiting factor at X?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A. Chlorophyll</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">B. Light intensity</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">C. Temperature</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">D. CO<sub>2</sub> concentration</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>B</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}